---
title: One-Pan Pork Carnitas Tacos with Cheese, Onion, and a Lime Crema
description: Think of this as a quicker, weeknight-friendly version of carnitas, one that doesn’t involve hours of slow-cooking like it typically would. To create that deep, warm profile in minimal time, you’ll add a spice blend and a bit of stock to ground pork, which makes it nice, rich, and saucy. It’s the centerpiece of these tacos, which come with lots of tasty toppings that everyone can add as they please.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-pork-carnita-tacos-d3a37bee.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-pork-carnita-tacos-5bc9f4deae08b509612bee22-898bc3fa.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 930 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-pork-carnita-tacos-5bc9f4deae08b509612bee22
time required: 25 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @red onion{1}. Finely chop one half; very
thinly slice other half from pole to pole. Core, seed, and finely chop
@poblano pepper{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{0.5%ounce}. Core and dice
@tomatoes{2}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges for serving.

Place sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{2%tsp},
@salt{0.5%tsp}, and @water{1%TBSP} in a #medium bowl{}. Toss until sugar and
salt are mostly dissolved. Set aside to marinate, tossing occasionally.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{20%ounce}, breaking up meat into pieces.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Transfer to a #plate{} using a #slotted spoon{}. Pour out and discard any
excess grease in pan.

Heat another large drizzle of @olive oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat.
Add chopped onion and poblano. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing,
until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Return pork to pan and add @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@tomato paste{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{2%TBSP}.
Cook, stirring, until everything comes together in a saucy mixture,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of salt
and pepper in a #small bowl{}. Stir in a splash or two of water to give
crema a drizzling consistency. Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{12} in a damp
#paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide filling, tomatoes, @monterey jack cheese{0.5%cup}, cilantro, pickled
onion, and crema between tortillas.

> TIP: You can put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone
> assemble their own tacos.

Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.